<h1><span><span id="ctl00_MainContentHolder_lblName">2011 Honda Odyssey Accessories and Parts</span></span></h1><span id="ctl00_MainContentHolder_lblContent">    <div style="clear: both; float: left; width: 650px;">
<br/><a href="http://www.bernardiparts.com/Departments/Accessories/Honda-Odyssey/2011.aspx" style="color:blue;font-weight:bold;">Shop for 2011 Honda Odyssey Accessories</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bernardiparts.com/SearchOptionsV7.aspx?Search=MODEL&ModelID=honda-odyssey-parts" style="color:blue;font-weight:bold;">Shop for 2011 Honda Odyssey Parts</a><br/><br/>
        Honda introduced a concept version of the 2011 Odyssey minivan at the Chicago Auto
        Show. Unlike the design of the all new for 2011 Toyota Sienna that <a href="http://www.familycarguide.com/blog/1035125_honda-toyota-and-nissan-to-offer-new-models-in-2011-year-of-the-minivan"
            target="_blank">Family Car Guide</a> describes as ""steady as she goes"", the
        design of the fourth generation Odyssey dramatically departs from conventional minivan
        styling. Its low and wide stance is highlighted by a "lightning-bolt" beltline that
        distinguishes the vehicle's profile.
        <br />
        <br />
        Compared to the current Odyssey, the concept version of the 2011 Honda Odyssey minivan
        offers a slightly lower roofline (-1.0 inch) and wider stance (+1.4 inch). This
        results in a sleeker, stronger and more dynamic presence. This newfound sleekness
        hints that the next Odyssey will be even more fun-to-drive.<br>
        <br>
        Enhanced aerodynamics and advanced power train technologies will contribute to a
        much improved fuel economy for the all new 2011 Honda Odyssey. The 2011 Odyssey
        minivan is expected to achieve an EPA-estimated fuel economy rating of 19 city/28
        highway miles-per gallon on select models compared to the 2010 Honda Odyssey Touring
        and Honda Odyssey EX minivan that are rated at 17/25 mpg, and the 2010 Honda Odyssey
        LX minivan at 16/23.
        <br />
        <br />
        According to <a href="http://www.familycarguide.com/blog/1035125_honda-toyota-and-nissan-to-offer-new-models-in-2011-year-of-the-minivan"
            target="_blank">Family Car Guide</a>, Honda has dropped plans for a diesel version
        of the 2011 Odyssey Minivan but still plans to offer a hybrid 2011 Odyssey minivan.
        <br>
        <br>
        Honda tells us that current Odyssey lovers can rest assured that everything they
        expect from an Odyssey—from functionality to sophistication to comfort, has been
        taken to higher levels in the 2011 Odyssey Minivan.
        <br>
        <br>
        BernardiParts.com will offer a full line of 2011 Honda Odyssey Accessories and 2011
        Honda Odyssey Parts for the all new Odyssey that is rumored to be released in the
        Fall of 2010. With a full line of Genuine 2011 Honda Odyssey Accessories and Genuine
        2011 Honda Odyssey Parts that will be offered at guaranteed lowest price on the
        internet, BernardiParts.com continues to be your one-stop-shop for adding a personalized
        touch to your Honda car, truck, minivan, and SUV.<br>
        <br>
        Here is the preliminary list of 2011 Odyssey Minivan Accessories.<br>

        <div style="float: right; border: 1px solid black; background-color: #E8E8E8; margin-top: 10px;
            width: 318px;">
            <b>Odyssey History</b> – <a href="http://www.turnto23.com/automotive/22500249/detail.html"
                target="“_blank”">TurnTo23.com</a>
            <ul>
                <li><b>1995</b> Honda first introduced the Odyssey in 1995. Back then, the minivan was
                    based on the popular Accord sedan and was available with only a 4-cylinder engine.
                    Unlike conventional minivans, the original Odyssey's rear doors opened like a car's
                    doors instead of sliding back as most vans' doors operate. </li>
                <li><b>1999</b> The Odyssey underwent a major redesign for the 1999 model year. The
                    minivan grew substantially in size - offering a V-6 engine and conventional sliding
                    minivan doors. </li>
                <li><b>2005</b> The minivan was last redesigned for the 2005 model year. That generation
                    sported the top-of-the-line Touring model which featured extra amenities.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="float: right; border: 1px solid black; background-color: #E8E8E8; margin-top: 10px;
            width: 318px;">
            <b>Recent Odyssey Honors</b>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Top selling</b> minivan since 2008!</li>
                <li><b>Edmunds.com</b> 2010 "Top Recommended" minivan award</li>
                <li><b>U.S. News and World Report</b> 2010 "Best Minivan for the Money" award</li>
                <li><b>Automotive Lease Guide</b> 2010 "Best Minivan for the Money," </li>
                <li><b>Kelley Blue Book</b>: one of the ten "Best New Family Vehicles of 2009"</li>
                <li><b>Kelley Blue Book</b>: "2009 Best Resale Value Award" in the van category</li></ul>
        </div>
